    Attack on Titan, a great section of a potentially wonderful anime.\
Attack on Titan is an anime that tries to go about itself differently than most other anime. It holds up a serious, grim tone and holds it up proudly. It tries to get past all of those stereotypical anime tropes of other shows, ending up with a very unique feeling to the anime. The show does contain some cliches of an action adventure, but it ends up handling them differently than what we've seen in the past.\
Story:\
Attack on Titan doesn't have much of a story where it's at, as it focuses more on a war\
          \
        between monsters and humans. The show has several mysterious elements that keep you interested in the show more than simply from its glorious action scenes and dialogue. The characters are also very diverse and all are given a decent amount of screen-time, some of the characters developing quite well. The story of this anime is simple in that it tells of the characters experiences in a world where mankind isn't in-charge. Although the show doesn't have much of a story in its own right, it never ends up answering a lot of questions you might have from the mysterious elements it puts forth. A second season seems like it would clear everything up, but this factor must be put out there.\
Attack on Titan is incomplete where it stands. It has Great entertainment value, but not very deep story-telling. This show is very much an action adventure~\
Art:\
Not much needs to be said on this front, as the art is Amazing. The equipment the humans use to fight these man-eating Titans is known as the 3D Maneuver Gear, and when these babies get screen-time, you'll be Very satisfied with what you witnessed. They work similar to spiderman's web-swinging powers, with the character swinging around buildings heading for the Titan's weak-spot.\
I do have some negatives to point out from this, however, that has personally stopped me from rewarding it a 10. The show works in two arcs, one arc being presented within a city. The city has many buildings and much room for 3D Maneuver Gear action. This potential action is wasted, however, as much of the city arc is filled with \"motivational\" filler. There will be long gaps of talking, which I usually wouldn't be bothered with, except this talking is meant to make a delusional character come back to reality and do their damn job. Every Time, these \"motivational\" sequences just don't feel right.\
Sound:\
The soundtrack is Badass and has plenty of themes you might want to listen to after the shows finished. One small gripe, for some people, might be the inclusion of Japanese/Engrish vocaled rock songs which can take you out of the show for a moment. Personally, this only affected me the first time it happened, and I enjoyed it after that.\
In my opinion, the soundtrack is great and really gets those feels going when it wants to~\
Characters:\
Firstly, I have to give this author kudos for not including some character cliches, from numerous other animes, with having all of these characters within it. The characters of this anime act reasonable, yet still stand out from one-another. These characters feel mortal. Every character in this show has the potential of dying, and it keeps the thrills going from that fact. There are plenty of characters, possibly too much for the shows own good, but each is given a reasonable amount of screen-time. Not every character is given enough character-development, however, leaving some characters forgetful. There is character-development in there though, and several characters do change (ones that you wouldn't expect).\
Now, I have a personal gripe about how the story played out and the choice the author made. At one point in the story, a new plot point is introduced that affects everything, and makes the show more exciting and mysterious in many ways. This does come with flaws, if you ask me, as how the show started out should have been held that way for longer. The main premise of the show doesn't need the inclusion of this element, and I would be happy to witness a Lot more 3D Maneuver Gear action during the show's first half.\
There was some failed chances at getting some major character developments as-well. At one point in the show, when the inclusion of this plot-element is put into place, the show throws away a chance at having an Amazing character development in the main character that would, literally, flip a cliche on itself. If the show took advantage of this, I would've been mind-blown, and the show would cease to have any cliches at all to make things even better.\
(It's hard to explain this point without spoilers, so thatâ€™s the best I can do~)\
Enjoyment:\
The show is extremely enjoyable if you're not searching for some deep plot. The show has many unanswered questions, and is stopped in a way that feels unfinished and unsatisfying. The show, however, Does satisfy on the way through. The action, the shock and awe~ This show had me drop my mouth one or twice.\
This is an exciting, and brutal, anime with plenty of death and gore. The fact these characters feel more able to die, no matter their place in the show, makes the excitement bar raise even higher.\
One flaw with the enjoyment is the reliance on episodes that end with something happening. The episode will push the event to happen and, right when it hits the wall, you have to wait for the next episode (not anymore since the shows out). This wouldn't be much of anything as it's exciting sometimes, but the show over-uses this to the point where you'll sigh when it happens for the fourth time. That is a lesser gripe, but still needs to be noted.\
Overall:\
I'd say watch it. Certainly watch it, in-fact. If your someone who requires their anime to be complete, that would be the only time I'd recommend waiting. This isn't an anime that should be skipped. There was a good amount of work poured into this anime, and they did a wonderful job. They also chose an interesting manga series to take into motion. This show is exciting, somewhat predictable, and very unique, not in its premise, but in the way it handles its premise.\
